        "Topic Identification and Description": "SUM OF N TERMS: Involves determining the total value obtained by adding a fixed number ($n$) of consecutive terms in an Arithmetic Progression, starting from the first term ($a_1$) and adding the common difference ($d$) sequentially. This uses the formula $S_n = \\frac{n}{2}[2a_1 + (n-1)d]$.",
        "Subtopic Differentiation": "Direct application of the sum formula given $a_1, d,$ and $n$."
      }
